## EPIC-01: User Authentication & Onboarding

**Priority:** P0 (Must Have)  
**Description:** Core authentication infrastructure enabling users to create accounts, authenticate securely, and manage their profile for the credit repair workflow.  
**Business Value:** Enables user identity management, data security, and personalized experience. Critical for all downstream features.  
**Dependencies:** Supabase Auth, Supabase Postgres (RLS policies)

### US-01: User Account Registration

**As a** new user,  
**I want to** create an account with my email and password,  
**So that** I can access the credit analysis and dispute features.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can register with email, password, and name
- [ ] Email verification is sent to user's email
- [ ] User cannot register with existing email
- [ ] Password meets minimum security requirements (8+ chars, mixed case, numbers)
- [ ] User is redirected to onboarding or dashboard after successful registration

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/auth/register`
- Use Supabase Auth for user creation
- Trigger email verification flow

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-02: User Authentication (Login)

**As a** registered user,  
**I want to** log in with my email and password,  
**So that** I can access my account and credit data securely.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can log in with email and password
- [ ] JWT token is returned and stored securely
- [ ] Invalid credentials show appropriate error message
- [ ] Session persists across browser restarts (refresh token)
- [ ] Rate limiting prevents brute force attacks

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/auth/login`
- Supabase Auth token management
- Redis-backed rate limiting (10 attempts/minute)

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-03: Password Reset Flow

**As a** user who forgot my password,  
**I want to** reset my password via email,  
**So that** I can regain access to my account.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can request password reset with email
- [ ] Reset link sent to registered email (expires in 1 hour)
- [ ] User can set new password via reset link
- [ ] Previous sessions are invalidated after password change
- [ ] Security event is logged

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/auth/password-reset/request`
- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/auth/password-reset/confirm`
- Use Supabase Auth password reset

**Estimation:** 2 story points

---

### US-04: User Profile Management

**As a** authenticated user,  
**I want to** view and update my profile information,  
**So that** I can keep my account details accurate.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can view their profile (email, name, created date)
- [ ] User can update their name and contact information
- [ ] Email changes require verification
- [ ] Profile updates are logged in audit trail
- [ ] Changes reflect immediately in the UI

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v1/users/me`
- Endpoint: `PATCH /api/v1/users/me`
- RLS policy: Users can only update their own profile

**Estimation:** 2 story points

---

## EPIC-02: Credit Report Upload & Ingestion

**Priority:** P0 (Must Have)  
**Description:** PDF credit report upload pipeline with async processing, status tracking, and error handling for bureau-agnostic analysis.  
**Business Value:** Core ingestion point for all downstream analysis. Must handle heterogeneous PDF formats reliably.  
**Dependencies:** Supabase Storage, Redis Queue, Document AI/OCR

### US-05: Credit Report PDF Upload

**As a** user,  
**I want to** upload my credit report PDF file,  
**So that** the system can begin analyzing my credit data.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can select and upload PDF files (max 10MB)
- [ ] Supported formats: PDF only
- [ ] File upload progress indicator shown
- [ ] Duplicate file detection with warning
- [ ] File stored in Supabase Storage with user association
- [ ] Upload confirmation with report ID returned

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/reports/upload`
- Multipart/form-data upload
- Virus scanning on upload
- Generate idempotency key for deduplication

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-06: Upload Status Tracking

**As a** user who uploaded a report,  
**I want to** check the processing status of my upload,  
**So that** I know when analysis is complete.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can view list of their uploaded reports
- [ ] Each report shows status: uploading, processing, completed, failed
- [ ] Processing progress indicator shown for in-progress reports
- [ ] Failed uploads show error reason
- [ ] Status updates in real-time (WebSocket or polling)

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v1/reports`
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v1/reports/{id}`
- WebSocket endpoint: `ws/reports/{id}/status`

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-07: Report Processing Pipeline

**As a** system,  
**I want to** process uploaded credit reports asynchronously,  
**So that** users aren't blocked during long-running OCR operations.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Upload triggers async job in Redis queue
- [ ] Job stages: upload → OCR extraction → parsing → tradeline detection → complete
- [ ] Each stage updates job status with progress
- [ ] Processing timeout after 5 minutes (with error)
- [ ] Failed jobs can be retried with same file
- [ ] Audit log captures processing metadata

**Technical Notes:**
- Redis job queue with status tracking
- Background worker for Document AI processing
- Retry mechanism with exponential backoff
- Job timeout enforcement

**Estimation:** 8 story points

---

### US-08: Upload Error Handling

**As a** user who encountered an upload error,  
**I want to** receive clear error messages and guidance,  
**So that** I can resolve the issue and successfully upload my report.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Invalid file types show clear rejection message
- [ ] Files exceeding size limit show appropriate error
- [ ] Corrupt/unreadable PDFs are rejected with guidance
- [ ] Network failures allow retry without data loss
- [ ] All errors logged with request_id for support
- [ ] Error messages are user-friendly, not technical

**Technical Notes:**
- Validation at upload endpoint
- Graceful error envelope with `request_id`
- Frontend displays localized error messages

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

## EPIC-03: Tradeline Extraction & Confidence Scoring

**Priority:** P0 (Must Have)  
**Description:** Bureau-agnostic tradeline extraction with confidence scoring, enabling accurate data capture across heterogeneous PDF layouts with auditability.  
**Business Value:** Core differentiating feature. 98% accuracy target for required fields, 100% for critical fields.  
**Dependencies:** Document AI/OCR, Normalization Service

### US-09: Tradeline Detection

**As a** system processing a credit report,  
**I want to** identify and segment individual tradelines within the document,  
**So that** each credit account can be analyzed separately.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] System detects tradeline sections across bureau formats (Experian, Equifax, TransUnion, CreditKarma)
- [ ] Handles multi-page reports with tradelines spanning pages
- [ ] Rejects non-credit-report documents with clear message
- [ ] Extracts all tradelines (minimum 90% recall)
- [ ] Processing completes within 2 minutes per PDF

**Technical Notes:**
- Document AI custom parser
- Layout analysis for section detection
- Configurable patterns for bureau detection

**Estimation:** 8 story points

---

### US-10: Critical Field Extraction

**As a** system extracting tradeline data,  
**I want to** capture critical fields with 100% accuracy,  
**So that** dispute letters contain no incorrect bureau or account data.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Bureau name extracted correctly (Experian, Equifax, TransUnion, etc.)
- [ ] Creditor name extracted with high accuracy
- [ ] Account number captured (masked appropriately for display)
- [ ] Account type identified (credit card, loan, mortgage, etc.)
- [ ] Account status extracted (open, closed, charged off, etc.)
- [ ] Critical field accuracy: 100%

**Technical Notes:**
- Priority fields: bureau, creditor, account_number, balance
- Validation rules for field correctness
- Integration with known bureau name patterns

**Estimation:** 8 story points

---

### US-11: Standard Field Extraction

**As a** system extracting tradeline data,  
**I want to** capture all required fields with 98% accuracy,  
**So that** users have complete credit data for review.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Current balance extracted (dollar amount)
- [ ] Credit limit/pull amount extracted (where applicable)
- [ ] Date opened extracted (MM/YYYY format)
- [ ] Positive/negative indicator identified (payment history based)
- [ ] Monthly payment amount extracted (where available)
- [ ] Per-field accuracy: 98% across all required fields

**Technical Notes:**
- Secondary extraction priority
- Currency normalization
- Date format standardization

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-12: Confidence Scoring

**As a** system,  
**I want to** assign confidence scores to each extracted field,  
**So that** users can focus review on low-confidence items.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Each extracted field has confidence score (0-100%)
- [ ] High confidence: 90-100% (auto-approved)
- [ ] Medium confidence: 70-89% (review recommended)
- [ ] Low confidence: <70% (user review required)
- [ ] Confidence score based on OCR quality, pattern matching, cross-validation
- [ ] Confidence factors are logged for debugging

**Technical Notes:**
- Confidence scoring service
- Threshold configuration
- Audit trail for low-confidence extractions

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-13: Low-Confidence Review UI

**As a** user reviewing extracted data,  
**I want to** see which fields need my attention,  
**So that** I can correct low-confidence extractions efficiently.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Low-confidence fields highlighted in tradeline view
- [ ] User can click to edit individual fields
- [ ] Original extraction shown alongside editable field
- [ ] Clear indicators for each confidence level
- [ ] Review progress tracked (items remaining)
- [ ] Bulk approve high-confidence items

**Technical Notes:**
- Frontend component: `ConfidenceIndicator`
- Edit modal for field correction
- Progress tracking in user session

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-14: Tradeline Display & Editing

**As a** user reviewing my extracted tradelines,  
**I want to** view and edit all tradeline data in a clear format,  
**So that** I can verify accuracy and make corrections.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Tradelines displayed in sortable table format
- [ ] Each tradeline expandable for full details
- [ ] Individual fields editable inline or in modal
- [ ] Changes saved with version tracking
- [ ] Undo/redo support for edits
- [ ] Keyboard navigation for efficiency

**Technical Notes:**
- Frontend: `TradelineTable` component
- Endpoint: `PATCH /api/v1/tradelines/{id}`
- Optimistic UI updates

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

## EPIC-04: Data Normalization & Validation

**Priority:** P0 (Must Have)  
**Description:** Data quality controls ensuring consistent formats, detecting anomalies, and maintaining data integrity across extraction pipeline.  
**Business Value:** Ensures downstream dispute processes use accurate, consistent data.  
**Dependencies:** Tradeline Extraction, Database

### US-15: Data Normalization Service

**As a** system,  
**I want to** normalize extracted data into consistent formats,  
**So that** all tradelines follow the same structure regardless of source format.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Currency values normalized to USD with consistent formatting
- [ ] Dates standardized to ISO-8601 (YYYY-MM-DD)
- [ ] Account types mapped to canonical values
- [ ] Status values normalized (open → active, etc.)
- [ ] Creditor names cleaned and standardized
- [ ] Missing fields handled consistently (null vs empty string)

**Technical Notes:**
- Normalization pipeline in `backend/services/normalization/`
- Pydantic schemas for validation
- Mapping tables for bureau-specific values

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-16: Missing Field Detection

**As a** system,  
**I want to** identify missing or incomplete fields in extracted data,  
**So that** users are aware of data gaps that may affect disputes.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Missing critical fields flagged immediately
- [ ] Missing standard fields flagged with severity level
- [ ] User notified of missing required data
- [ ] Guidance provided for manual entry
- [ ] Missing data tracked for accuracy metrics
- [ ] Report includes completeness score

**Technical Notes:**
- Field requirement configuration
- Notification trigger for missing data
- Manual entry form for missing fields

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-17: Data Validation Rules

**As a** system,  
**I want to** validate extracted data against business rules,  
**So that** errors and inconsistencies are caught before dispute generation.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Balance amounts are non-negative (except for negative balances)
- [ ] Date opened is not in the future
- [ ] Credit limit >= current balance (where applicable)
- [ ] Account numbers pass format validation
- [ ] Creditor names meet minimum length
- [ ] Validation errors surfaced to user for correction

**Technical Notes:**
- Pydantic validators in schema definitions
- Custom validation rules in normalization service
- Validation result in API response

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-18: Data Lineage Tracking

**As a** system maintaining auditability,  
**I want to** track each field back to its source in the original PDF,  
**So that** disputes can cite original data and errors can be traced.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Each extracted field linked to source PDF location
- [ ] Original OCR text preserved for audit
- [ ] Extraction version tracking for each tradeline
- [ ] User can view source context for any field
- [ ] Lineage data included in export/reports
- [ ] Compliance with data retention requirements

**Technical Notes:**
- Lineage table in database
- PDF chunk storage with reference
- Source viewer UI component

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-19: Quality Indicators

**As a** system,  
**I want to** expose quality metrics for extracted data,  
**So that** users and admins can assess reliability.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Overall extraction quality score per report
- [ ] Per-field quality breakdown available
- [ ] Comparison to benchmark accuracy
- [ ] Quality trends over multiple reports
- [ ] Admin dashboard shows aggregate quality metrics
- [ ] Quality data included in dispute audit trail

**Technical Notes:**
- Quality scoring algorithm
- Aggregation service for metrics
- Admin analytics endpoint

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

## EPIC-05: Dispute Packet Generation

**Priority:** P0 (Must Have)  
**Description:** Automated dispute letter and packet generation with 100% data correctness, document assembly, and download capability.  
**Business Value:** Core value delivery - generates ready-to-mail dispute packets from credit data.  
**Dependencies:** Tradeline Extraction, Document Upload, Notification Service

### US-20: Dispute Letter Template System

**As a** system generating disputes,  
**I want to** use configurable letter templates,  
**So that** dispute letters meet legal requirements and are customized per situation.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Template engine supports variable substitution
- [ ] Templates include required legal language
- [ ] Multiple template types (personal, business, rapid)
- [ ] Template versioning with audit trail
- [ ] Admin can manage template content
- [ ] Templates support bureau-specific variations

**Technical Notes:**
- Template storage in database
- Jinja2 or similar templating engine
- Template validation on save

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-21: Automated Letter Generation

**As a** user,  
**I want to** generate dispute letters for selected tradelines,  
**So that** I can dispute inaccurate information on my credit report.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can select tradelines for dispute
- [ ] System generates letter with dispute language
- [ ] Letter includes user info, bureau info, tradeline details
- [ ] Generation completes within 1 minute
- [ ] Preview available before finalizing
- [ ] Rate limit: 3 generations per user per day

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/disputes/letters`
- Letter generation service
- PDF generation via pdf-lib or jspdf

**Estimation:** 8 story points

---

### US-22: Data Correctness Validation

**As a** system generating dispute letters,  
**I want to** validate all data before letter creation,  
**So that** dispute letters contain no incorrect information.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] All critical fields verified before generation
- [ ] Any discrepancy blocks generation with explanation
- [ ] Validation report shown to user
- [ ] Low-confidence fields require explicit confirmation
- [ ] Generation blocked if required data missing
- [ ] Audit log of validation decisions

**Technical Notes:**
- Pre-generation validation service
- Block mechanism with error response
- User confirmation flow for edge cases

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-23: Packet Assembly

**As a** system,  
**I want to** assemble complete dispute packets with all required documents,  
**So that** users have everything needed for mailing.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Packet includes: dispute letter, copy of credit report, ID documents, cover letter
- [ ] Documents organized in correct order
- [ ] Bureau-specific labels and addressing
- [ ] Page numbering and table of contents
- [ ] Checklists included for operator review
- [ ] Packet generation timestamp recorded

**Technical Notes:**
- PDF assembly service
- Document ordering logic
- Template for packet structure

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-24: Packet Download

**As a** DIY user,  
**I want to** download my complete dispute packet,  
**So that** I can print and mail it myself.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Download available as PDF (zip for multi-page)
- [ ] File size appropriate for download
- [ ] Download includes assembly instructions
- [ ] Download count tracked for analytics
- [ ] Download link expires after 7 days
- [ ] Secure download with user authentication

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v1/disputes/{id}/packet`
- Signed URLs for secure download
- CDN caching for performance

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-25: DIY Mailing Instructions

**As a** DIY user,  
**I want to** receive clear mailing instructions with my packet,  
**So that** I can correctly mail my dispute to the right bureau.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Step-by-step mailing instructions included
- [ ] Bureau mailing addresses provided
- [ ] Certified mail recommendations
- [ ] Timeline expectations set
- [ ] Tracking recommendations
- [ ] Follow-up guidance included

**Technical Notes:**
- Instruction template
- Bureau address database
- Integration with USPS address verification

**Estimation:** 2 story points

---

## EPIC-06: Document Upload & Verification

**Priority:** P1 (Should Have)  
**Description:** Identity and supporting document upload for dispute fulfillment, with storage and verification status tracking.  
**Business Value:** Required for dispute packets. Missing documents block packet completion.  
**Dependencies:** Supabase Storage, User Authentication

### US-26: Identity Document Upload

**As a** user,  
**I want to** upload my ID and SSN card,  
**So that** I can complete the document requirements for dispute packets.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can upload government ID (front/back)
- [ ] User can upload SSN card
- [ ] Accepted formats: JPG, PNG, PDF (max 5MB each)
- [ ] Documents associated with user account
- [ ] Upload confirmation with document type
- [ ] Duplicate detection prevents double upload

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `POST /api/v1/documents/upload`
- Document type enumeration: id_card, ssn_card, utility_bill
- Storage bucket: `user-documents`

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-27: Supporting Document Upload

**As a** user,  
**I want to** upload a utility bill as proof of address,  
**So that** I can complete my dispute packet requirements.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can upload utility bill (electric, gas, water, internet)
- [ ] Bill must be within 90 days
- [ ] Name and address on bill must match user profile
- [ ] Document stored securely with encryption
- [ ] Verification status tracked
- [ ] Rejected documents show rejection reason

**Technical Notes:**
- Document type: utility_bill
- Date validation on upload
- Address matching logic

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-28: Document Verification Status

**As a** user,  
**I want to** see the status of my uploaded documents,  
**So that** I know when my packet is complete.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Dashboard shows document completeness
- [ ] Each document shows status: pending, verified, rejected
- [ ] Rejected documents show reason and guidance
- [ ] Missing documents clearly indicated
- [ ] Notification when all documents verified
- [ ] Document upload history accessible

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v1/documents`
- Status tracking in database
- Notification trigger on verification

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-29: Document Re-upload Flow

**As a** user with a rejected document,  
**I want to** replace my rejected document,  
**So that** I can resolve verification issues quickly.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can view rejection reason
- [ ] User can upload replacement document
- [ ] Previous rejected document archived
- [ ] Verification process restarts automatically
- [ ] User notified of new verification status
- [ ] History of all uploads preserved

**Technical Notes:**
- Document versioning
- Archive storage for rejected docs
- Status update notifications

**Estimation:** 2 story points

