## EPIC-07: Dispute Monitoring & Status Tracking

**Priority:** P1 (Should Have)  
**Description:** Dispute lifecycle tracking from generation through mailing to resolution, with timeline and history.  
**Business Value:** Users need visibility into dispute progress. Critical for retention and trust.  
**Dependencies:** Dispute Generation, Database

### US-30: Dispute Dashboard

**As a** user,  
**I want to** see all my disputes in a single dashboard,  
**So that** I can track progress across all my credit repair efforts.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] All disputes listed with current status
- [ ] Status categories: draft, ready, mailed, in-progress, resolved
- [ ] Summary statistics (total, by status)
- [ ] Quick actions for each dispute
- [ ] Sortable and filterable list
- [ ] Search functionality

**Technical Notes:**
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v1/disputes`
- Frontend: `DisputeDashboard` page
- React Query for data fetching

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-31: Dispute Status Timeline

**As a** user,  
**I want to** see the detailed timeline of my dispute,  
**So that** I understand what has happened and what comes next.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Timeline shows all status changes with timestamps
- [ ] Milestone markers: created, reviewed, mailed, received, resolved
- [ ] Expected next steps displayed
- [ ] Resolution status when available
- [ ] Exportable timeline for records
- [ ] Email notifications for status changes

**Technical Notes:**
- Dispute status enum and transitions
- Timeline table in database
- Webhook for external status updates

**Estimation:** 5 story points

---

### US-32: Dispute History

**As a** user,  
**I want to** access historical records of my past disputes,  
**So that** I can reference previous credit repair efforts.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] All past disputes archived and accessible
- [ ] Downloadable copies of generated packets
- [ ] Outcome tracking (success, partial, unsuccessful)
- [ ] Historical comparison view
- [ ] Export functionality (CSV/PDF)
- [ ] Data retention compliance

**Technical Notes:**
- Archive storage for completed disputes
- Long-term retention in database
- Export service

**Estimation:** 3 story points

---

### US-33: Resolution Tracking

**As a** user,  
**I want to** update my dispute with resolution results,  
**So that** I can track which negative items have been removed.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can mark dispute as resolved
- [ ] Resolution options: removed, updated, no change
- [ ] If removed, specify which tradelines
- [ ] Updated tradelines show new status
- [ ] Success metrics tracked
- [ ] Before/after comparison available

**Technical Notes:**
- Resolution update endpoint
- Tradeline status update integration
- Metrics aggregation

**Estimation:** 3 story points

