## Dependencies Matrix

```
US-05 (Upload) → US-07 (Pipeline) → US-09 (Detection) → US-10 (Critical Fields)
                                                                   ↓
US-01 (Register) ──→ US-02 (Login) ──→ US-05 (Upload) ───────────────→ US-11 (Standard Fields)
                                                                   ↓
                                           US-15 (Normalization) ← US-21 (Letter Generation)
                                                                   ↓
US-26 (Documents) ─────────────────────────→ US-23 (Packet Assembly) → US-24 (Download)
```

---

## Risk Factors

1. **Extraction Accuracy (High Risk):** US-09 through US-14 are critical path. Consider spike investigation if accuracy targets at risk.
2. **Third-Party Dependencies:** Lob.com integration (US-36) and Document AI may have availability risks.
3. **Scope Creep:** Dispute letter templates (US-20) may require more complexity than anticipated.
4. **Payment Integration:** US-35 requires PCI compliance and security review.

---

## Success Criteria per Sprint

**Sprint 1:** Users can register, login, upload credit reports, and track processing status.

**Sprint 2:** Users see extracted tradelines with confidence scores, can review low-confidence items, and data is normalized.

**Sprint 3:** Users can generate dispute packets, upload required documents, and receive notifications.

**Sprint 4:** Users can track dispute status, admins have monitoring tools, paid fulfillment works end-to-end.

**Sprint 5:** Developers have testing tools, regression tests run automatically, documentation is complete.

